    <string name="mic_permission_why_button">Why?</string>
    <string name="mic_permission_explanation_title">Why is microphone permission needed?</string>
    <string name="mic_permission_explanation_body">Starting from Android 10, capturing internal audio requires the MediaProjection API, which always requires the RECORD_AUDIO permission, even if you only intend to capture system audio and not the microphone. This is a precautionary measure enforced by the OS: the audio pipeline is initialized as a single unit, and the system requests the permission upfront without knowing in advance which source will be used. Additionally, some OEM implementations (Samsung, Xiaomi, and others) enforce this requirement more strictly than stock Android, making the permission effectively mandatory in all cases.</string>
